  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dba\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Free urea to farmers will arrive in a fortnight",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Agriculture Minister Mahinda Amaraweera said that 1,000 metric tons of urea fertilizers provided free of charge to Sri Lankan farmers by the World Food and Agriculture Organization will be received in Sri Lanka within the next fortnight.",
        "The World Food and Agriculture Organization had agreed to provide 375,000 50 kg bags of urea fertilizer to low-income farming families in Sri Lanka for rice cultivation.",
        "According to the Ministry of Agriculture, this stock of urea fertilizer is going to be given free of charge to 375,000 farmers who have less than an acre of paddy fields at the rate of 50 kg per farmer.",
        "After a discussion with the officials of the World Food and Agriculture Organization, Agriculture Minister Mahinda Amaraweera agreed to provide free urea fertilizer for the high season.",
        "The Minister of Agriculture said that the first batch of 1000 metric tons will be received in the next two weeks."
      ],
